\"Python Package Index (PyPI)\", \"url\": \"https://pypi.org\" }, { \"name\": \"Global Module Index\", \"url\": \"https://docs.python.org/3/py-modindex.html\" }, { \"name\": \"Glossary\", \"url\": \"https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html\" } ] } ] } </file> <file name=\"file_20---823d488a-a90f-4b7e-b32a-b4956314a381.json\" mime=\"application/json\"> { \"title\": \"Redis Documentation\", \"metadata\": { \"source\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/\", \"generated_at\": \"2026-02-11T13:14:44.778817Z\", \"version\": \"Redis 8.x\", \"license\": \"Redis Source Available License (RSALv2) / Server Side Public License (SSPLv1)\" }, \"sections\": [ { \"id\": \"overview\", \"title\": \"Welcome to Redis Docs\", \"description\": \"Redis is an open-source, in-memory data structure store used as a database, cache, message broker, and streaming engine.\", \"content\": { \"get_started\": [ { \"name\": \"Redis Cloud quick start\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/operate/rc/rc-quickstart/\", \"description\": \"Set up a Free Redis-managed database on AWS, GCP, or Azure.\" }, { \"name\": \"Get started with Redis Open Source\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/get-started/\", \"description\": \"Install and start using Redis locally.\" } ], \"genai\": [ { \"name\": \"Redis with RAG\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/get-started/rag/\", \"description\": \"Get started using Redis for retrieval augmented generation.\" }, { \"name\": \"Redis for AI docs and code examples\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/ai/\", \"description\": \"AI-focused documentation and examples.\" } ], \"client_libraries\": [ { \"name\": \"Python (redis-py)\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/redis-py/\" }, { \"name\": \"C#/.NET\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/dotnet/\" }, { \"name\": \"JavaScript/Node.js\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/nodejs/\" }, { \"name\": \"Java (Jedis)\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/jedis/\" }, { \"name\": \"Go\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/go/\" }, { \"name\": \"PHP\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/php/\" } ], \"tools\": [ { \"name\": \"Redis CLI\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/tools/cli/\", \"description\": \"Command-line interface for Redis.\" }, { \"name\": \"Redis Insight\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/tools/insight/\", \"description\": \"GUI tool for Redis database visualization.\" }, { \"name\": \"Redis for VSCode\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/tools/redis-for-vscode/\", \"description\": \"Visual Studio Code extension.\" } ] } }, { \"id\": \"data_types\", \"title\": \"Data Types\", \"description\": \"Redis implements the following data types for various use cases.\", \"content\": { \"core_types\": [ { \"name\": \"Strings\", \"description\": \"The most basic Redis data type, representing a sequence of bytes.\" }, { \"name\": \"Lists\", \"description\": \"Lists of strings sorted by insertion order.\" }, { \"name\": \"Sets\", \"description\": \"Unordered collections of unique strings with O(1) add/remove/test.\" }, { \"name\": \"Hashes\", \"description\": \"Record types modeled as collections of field-value pairs.\" }, { \"name\": \"Sorted Sets\", \"description\": \"Collections of unique strings ordered by associated score.\" } ], \"advanced_types\": [ { \"name\": \"Vector Sets\", \"description\": \"High-dimensional vector data for ML, recommendations, semantic search. Supports HNSW algorithm and cosine similarity.\" }, { \"name\": \"Streams\", \"description\": \"Append-only log data structure for recording events in order.\" }, { \"name\": \"Geospatial Indexes\", \"description\": \"Finding locations within geographic radius or bounding box.\" }, { \"name\": \"Bitmaps\", \"description\": \"Bitwise operations on strings.\" }, { \"name\": \"Bitfields\", \"description\": \"Multiple counters with atomic get/set/increment operations.\" }, { \"name\": \"JSON\", \"description\": \"Structured, hierarchical arrays and key-value objects matching JSON format.\" } ], \"probabilistic_types\": [ { \"name\": \"HyperLogLog\", \"description\": \"Probabilistic estimates of set cardinality.\" }, { \"name\": \"Bloom Filter\", \"description\": \"Check for presence/absence of an element in a set.\" }, { \"name\": \"Cuckoo Filter\", \"description\": \"Similar to Bloom filters with different trade-offs.\" }, { \"name\": \"t-digest\", \"description\": \"Approximate percentile/quantile estimation.\" }, { \"name\": \"Top-K\", \"description\": \"Track most frequent items.\" }, { \"name\": \"Count-min Sketch\", \"description\": \"Approximate frequency counting.\" } ], \"time_series\": { \"name\": \"Time Series\", \"description\": \"Dedicated time series data type for IoT, monitoring, financial data.\" } } }, { \"id\": \"deploy_operate\", \"title\": \"Deploy and Operate\", \"content\": { \"deployment\": [ { \"name\": \"Redis deployment planning\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/operate/rs/installing-upgrading/install/plan-deployment/\" }, { \"name\": \"Active-Active geo-distributed Redis\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/operate/rs/databases/active-active/\" }, { \"name\": \"Kubernetes deployment guide\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/operate/kubernetes/deployment/quick-start/\" }, { \"name\": \"OpenShift deployment\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/operate/kubernetes/deployment/openshift/\" } ], \"data_management\": [ { \"name\": \"Redis Input/Output Tool (RIOT)\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/integrate/riot/\", \"description\": \"Migrate data from files, databases, or snapshots.\" }, { \"name\": \"Redis Data Integration\", \"url\": \"https://redis.io/docs/latest/integrate/redis-data-integration/\", \"description\": \"Sync with live data from disk-based databases.\" } ], \"monitoring\": [ { \"name\": \"Prometheus with Redis Enterpris